values:
This is by far, without a doubt, the worst break from school EVER.&nbsp; EVER.

First draft of my 20-25 page paper on the Decembrists due tuesday, I only need 10-15 pages by then.&nbsp; I have 13 written, but it's going to need some big changes in the next month.&nbsp; A lot of work still to do on it.&nbsp; But between today ad yesterday, I got 13 pages written.&nbsp; more than halfway... but like i said, a lot still to do.&nbsp; 

thursday i spent all day reading the quiet american by graham greene, and then writing a paper on it, which i finished at 4AM.&nbsp; I may have TOTALLY missed the point on the paper, or i may have hit exactly what he wanted me to write about.&nbsp; so... we'll see.&nbsp; Friday i did more research for my other paper.&nbsp; which i've been doing daily for the past week or two now...

Finally tonight, when i finished my 13 pages of writing, you'd think 'im done.&nbsp; no.

i have a small debate paper for international relations due tuesday.&nbsp; I don't even know what i'm supposed to do.&nbsp; at first i thought it was a 500 word limit, but that looks like it's the RESPONSES that are 500 word limits.&nbsp; the class is online, and all assignments get posted online.&nbsp; of the 4 people who posted theirs, two have long, 6 page papers filled with research and quotes everywhere.&nbsp; the other two have three research sources (what he wants), and basically 300 words of their own writing,and then just huge ass quotes.&nbsp; 

i think i'll go with the second way of doing it.&nbsp; this class is such a pain in the ass.&nbsp; i'm hoping to salvage an A, since it really isn't that diffcult.&nbsp; but, i'll probably end up with a B.&nbsp; hopefully no worse.&nbsp; 

Oh, yeah, I also have a huge test on wednesday, that i need to work on.&nbsp; I have to outline NINE essay questions.&nbsp; each outline will probably be a page or two.&nbsp; so, i have to do that between monday and tuesday as well.

and i need to start looking into schools to go to after villanova to get a masters in education.&nbsp; so far i've only really looked into cabrini.&nbsp; but i want to look at west chester, drexel, penn, temple, penn state, and... i think that's it?&nbsp; maybe others.&nbsp; villanova requires so many pre-requisite classes, that i'd need a whole other semester just to be able to enter.&nbsp; hopefully the other schools aren't as strict.&nbsp; 

ugh.&nbsp; 

despite all this work, nothing else has really been going well this weekend either.&nbsp;&nbsp; oh well... 

hahaha.&nbsp; john kruk just said that he's reading "The Brothers Kouzmanoff"&nbsp; hilarious.&nbsp; to me anyway.

ok, i think i've done enough work today, i'm going to play MLB 2k7.&nbsp;&nbsp;
